    23→For example, if you have a backend called `mdbook-wordcount`, then you can include it with:
    59→### Custom backend commands
    60→
    61→By default when you add an `[output.foo]` table to your `book.toml` file,
    62→`mdbook` will try to invoke the `mdbook-foo` executable.
    63→If you want to use a different program name or pass in command-line arguments,
    64→this behaviour can be overridden by adding a `command` field.
    71→### Optional backends
