    84→## HTML renderer options
    85→
    86→The HTML renderer has a variety of options detailed below.
    87→They should be specified in the `[output.html]` table of the `book.toml` file.
   176→### `[output.html.print]`
   177→
   178→The `[output.html.print]` table provides options for controlling the printable output.
   179→By default, mdBook will include an icon on the top right of the book (which looks like <i class="fas fa-print"></i>) that will print the book as a single page.
   191→### `[output.html.fold]`
   192→
   193→The `[output.html.fold]` table provides options for controlling folding of the chapter listing in the navigation sidebar.
   206→### `[output.html.playground]`
   207→
   208→The `[output.html.playground]` table provides options for controlling Rust sample code blocks, and their integration with the [Rust Playground].
   230→### `[output.html.code]`
   231→
   232→The `[output.html.code]` table provides options for controlling code blocks.
   244→### `[output.html.search]`
   245→
   246→The `[output.html.search]` table provides options for controlling the built-in text [search].
   247→mdBook must be compiled with the `search` feature enabled (on by default).
   286→#### `[output.html.search.chapter]`
   287→
   288→The [`output.html.search.chapter`] table provides the ability to modify search settings per chapter or directory. Each key is the path to the chapter source file or directory, and the value is a table of settings to apply to that path. This will merge recursively, with more specific paths taking precedence.
   300→### `[output.html.redirect]`
   301→
   302→The `[output.html.redirect]` table provides a way to add redirects.
   303→This is useful when you move, rename, or remove a page to ensure that links to the old URL will go to the new location.
   325→## Markdown renderer
   326→
   327→The Markdown renderer will run preprocessors and then output the resulting
   328→Markdown. This is mostly useful for debugging preprocessors, especially in
   329→conjunction with `mdbook test` to see the Markdown that `mdbook` is passing
   330→to `rustdoc`.
